\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Acceptance Criteria\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Tier:** T1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Instructions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Read the failing test or bug report to understand the core issue.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Make the minimal code change required to fix the problem.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Run the relevant tests to confirm the fix and ensure no regressions were introduced.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. Commit the change with a clear commit message: `fix(scope): summary [T-021@20260416T181925Z]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not expand scope; address only the reported problem.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Follow existing code style and patterns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not clean, revert, commit, or otherwise normalize unrelated pre-existing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  workspace changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Commit your working change immediately.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Validation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRun this command before finishing:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npytest tests/ -x --tb=short && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\\\