solo`, `tacet`) is correctly parsed and respected, with the rule only applying to voices explicitly tagged as followers.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Completeness\\\\\\\\n+The task is complete according to the acceptance criteria:\\\\\\\\n+- `CallResponseRule` implemented in `render/rules/call_response.py`.\\\\\\\\n+- Correct transformations for building and pausing states.\\\\\\\\n+- Metadata role parsing covers all required keys and values.\\\\\\\\n+- Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_call_response.py` verifies both functional behavior and role-based filtering.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Consistency\\\\\\\\n+The implementation is consistent with other \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tier 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" render rules in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/` (e.g., `phrase_arch.py`, `articulation.py`). It uses the shared `Event` data model and follows the `role_is_eligible` contract established in `role_gate.py`. Although `PerformanceIntent` was mentioned in the spec, it is not yet present in the codebase (targeted for T-030), and the use of the `Event` model for these transformations is the correct adaptation for the current project state.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\n+No security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. The implementation consists of pure-function mathematical transformations on local data structures.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\n+The code quality is high, with clear documentation, clean dataclass abstractions, and robust role-parsing logic. The tests use Pearson correlation to verify complementarity, which is a rigorous approach for validating musical behavior.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Issues Found\\\\\\\\n+- None.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\n+The implementation successfully realizes the call-response gating requirement. The adaptation to use the `Event` model in the absence of `PerformanceIntent` is appropriate. Recurring hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be satisfied in the current daemon startup paths.\\\\\\\"}\\\\n+{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:12.389Z\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"I'll\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\":true}\\\\n+{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:12.406Z\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\" update `progress.md` to mark T-024 as complete and include the relevant logs, ensuring the SDP\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\":true}\\\\n+\\\\n+codex\\\\n+The dirty state is entirely generated SDP tracking: progress, run logs, notifications, telemetry, and an untracked canonical T-024 verification report that complements an earlier misnamed report. I’m staging those artifacts now so the tree can be committed and left clean.\\\\n+exec\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'git add -A' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\n+ succeeded in 109ms:\\\\n+exec\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'git status --short' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\n+ succeeded in 0ms:\\\\n+M  progress.md\\\\n+M  sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Zb_1776395654.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Zc_1776395895.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260416T181925Z_1776396842.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-023_20260416T181925Z_1776397430.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-025_20260416T181925Z_1776398857.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-026_20260416T181925Z_1776399250.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-027_20260416T181925Z_1776399901.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-028_20260416T181925Z_1776400429.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-029_20260416T181925Z_1776400962.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-030_20260416T181925Z_1776401478.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-031_20260416T181925Z_1776401815.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-032_20260416T181925Z_1776402396.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-033_20260416T181925Z_1776402787.log\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-034_20260416T181925Z_1776403295.