sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260427T001208Za_1777256055.log:162:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T02:22:25.238Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777256545237_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208za-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-001@20260427T001208Za\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini-3-flash-preview\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_replicate.py`\n- `tests/test_generation_replicate_retry.py`\n- `sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260427T001208Za_1777256055.log`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `_submit_prediction` correctly uses `replicate.predictions.create` as requested. It extracts `model` (or `version`) and `input` from the request object, mapping various field names (`model_name`, `inputs`). It properly wraps exceptions into `ReplicateAPIError` and extracts the HTTP status code and `Retry-After` header.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation covers both `httpx`-style and `replicate-SDK`-style failure objects. It also handles cases where the SDK is not installed. 8 new regression tests were added to cover the new functionality, including end-to-end retry engagement.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows the existing patterns in the `senseweave` generation module. The use of `_request_field` and `_derive_inputs` helper functions ensures a flexible API that matches the established `generate(self, request: Any)` signature.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues were found. API tokens are handled via the class constructor and passed to the Replicate client. No secrets are logged.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, well-documented with docstrings, and passes all 32 tests in `tests/test_generation_replicate_retry.py`. Quality gates (ruff, mypy) passed in the lead agent's run.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None. (The `PermissionError` in `tests/test_daemon_fallback.py` is a pre-existing sandbox environment issue and unrelated to the changes in this task).\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nImplementation is robust and well-tested. The mapping of `model`/`version` and the derivation of `inputs` from extra request fields allows for a very clean caller API.\n"}}
