sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:23:The current implementation is a useful foundation but is not yet the full "minimal operator involvement" PAL system. This PRD defines the end-to-end build needed to let SDP frontier models implement, verify, and deploy a complete PAL 2026 agentic operations platform.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:27:1. Maintain a project knowledge base from PAL docs, runbooks, smoke reports, deployment state, and run artifacts.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:32:6. Verify its own work through tests, live health checks, smoke runs, and deployment probes.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:68:The SDP implementation must preserve compatibility with this current deployed shape while still allowing later Docker/systemd variants.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:74:1. Build PAL into a complete agentic operations layer for the current Phase 1 deployment.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:78:5. Add deployment automation that can safely update the live PAL host and verify it after deploy.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:86:- No H100 rental, Qwen3-235B deployment, or persistent Vast volume migration.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:89:- No unrestricted remote shell.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:105:- Writing or deleting remote config files.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:123:The remote PAL router remains a FastAPI service in front of Ollama. This PRD may add endpoints only when needed for safe operations, such as structured status or metrics. The existing `/health` and `/query` endpoints must remain backward compatible.
